### Interview + Resume Parsing — ALL IN ONE (for REST Client / VS Code)
### Replace placeholders: http://localhost:8000 -> http://localhost:8000
### Replace {{SESSION_ID}} and {{UPLOAD_ID}} after responses. Replace file path with your local resume path.

####################
### 1) CREATE SESSION (create interview session)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/interview/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "candidate_name": "Test Candidate",
  "role": "Software Engineer"
}

###

####################
### 2) READ SESSIONS (list all interviews / sessions)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/interview/

###

####################
### 3) READ ONE SESSION (replace 1 with actual interview id)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/interview/1/

###

####################
### 4) UPLOAD RESUME (multipart/form-data)
### Replace SESSION_ID below with the session_id from step 1 response
POST http://localhost:8000/api/resume-upload/
Content-Type: multipart/form-data

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="session_id"

{{SESSION_ID}}
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="role"

Software Engineer
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="resume"; filename="test_resume.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./test_resume.pdf
--boundary--

###
# Alternative (REST Client supports @ file upload): uncomment and use if supported by your client
# POST http://localhost:8000/api/resume-upload/
# Content-Type: multipart/form-data
#
# session_id={{SESSION_ID}}
# role=Software Engineer
# resume=@/absolute/path/to/test_resume.pdf

###

####################
### 5) LIST UPLOADS (filter by session_id)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/resume-upload/?session_id={{SESSION_ID}}

###

####################
### 6) GET UPLOAD DETAIL (replace UPLOAD_ID with id from step 5)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/resume-upload/{{UPLOAD_ID}}/

###

####################
### 7) TRIGGER / CHECK PARSING RESULT
### If your API exposes a parse-result endpoint or stores parsed summary in upload detail, use the upload detail above.
### Example: polling parsed summary field from upload detail
GET http://localhost:8000/api/resume-upload/{{UPLOAD_ID}}/?fields=parsed_summary

###

####################
### 8) START / CONTINUE INTERVIEW (send answer or start flow)
### Use session_id returned during creation
POST http://localhost:8000/api/interview/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{SESSION_ID}}",
  "answer": "Ready to start the interview"
}

###

####################
### 9) NEXT INTERVIEW STEP (reply to the question returned by the API)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/interview/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{SESSION_ID}}",
  "answer": "My answer to the last question"
}

###

####################
### 10) GET INTERVIEW STATE / PROGRESS
### If your API supports GET by session (otherwise replace with numeric interview id)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/interview/?session_id={{SESSION_ID}}

###
# or
GET http://localhost:8000/api/interview/1/

###

####################
### 11) DELETE SESSION (if supported)
DELETE http://localhost:8000/api/interview/1/

###

####################
### Quick curl equivalents (copy-paste if you prefer curl)

# Create session
# curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/interview/ -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"candidate_name":"Test Candidate","role":"Software Engineer"}'

# Upload resume (curl)
# curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/resume-upload/ -F "session_id={{SESSION_ID}}" -F "role=Software Engineer" -F "resume=@/path/to/test_resume.pdf"

# Continue interview
# curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/interview/ -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"session_id":"{{SESSION_ID}}","answer":"Answer text"}'
